text.section:
"Primary supervising physician" means a physician who:
Completes a delegation agreement that meets the requirements under §§ 15-301(d) and (e) and 15-302 of this title and files a copy with the Board;
Acts as the physician responsible to ensure that a physician assistant practices medicine in accordance with this title and the regulations adopted under this title;
Ensures that a physician assistant practices within the scope of practice of the primary supervising physician or any designated alternate supervising physician; and
Ensures that a list of alternate supervising physicians is maintained at the practice setting.
